datasets.name: 37d08591
datasets.query:
SELECT
  subscription_id,
  resource_group,
  storage_account,
  table_catalog,
  table_schema,
  table_name,
  full_namespace,
  storage_path,
  table_type,
  data_source_format,
  authType,
  authObjectId,
  userAgentHeader,
  CASE
    WHEN
      lower(userAgentHeader) like '%databricks%'
      OR lower(userAgentHeader) like '%dbr%'
      OR lower(userAgentHeader) like '%apn/1.0 unknown%'
    THEN
      'databricks'
    ELSE 'external'
  END as requester,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN category = 'StorageWrite' THEN 1
      ELSE 0
    END
  ) AS StorageWrite,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN category = 'StorageDelete' THEN 1
      ELSE 0
    END
  ) AS StorageDelete,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN category = 'StorageRead' THEN 1
      ELSE 0
    END
  ) AS StorageRead
FROM
  slog.default.azure_storage_logs
GROUP BY
  subscription_id,
  resource_group,
  storage_account,
  table_catalog,
  table_schema,
  table_name,
  full_namespace,
  storage_path,
  table_type,
  data_source_format,
  authType,
  authObjectId,
  userAgentHeader,
  requester

datasets.name: 89a92a69
datasets.query:
with cte_details as (
  SELECT 
    storage_time,
    subscription_id,
    resource_group,
    storage_account,
    table_catalog,
    table_schema,
    table_name,
    full_namespace,
    storage_path,
    table_type,
    data_source_format,
    category,
    operationName,
    statusText,
    durationMs,
    callerIpAddress,
    authType,
    authObjectId,
    userAgentHeader,
    clientRequestId,
    objectKey,
    CASE
      WHEN
        lower(userAgentHeader) like '%databricks%'
        OR lower(userAgentHeader) like '%dbr%'
        OR lower(userAgentHeader) like '%apn/1.0 unknown%'
      THEN
        'databricks'
      ELSE 'external'
    END as requester
  from slog.default.azure_storage_logs
)
SELECT
  subscription_id,
  resource_group,
  storage_account,
  table_catalog,
  table_schema,
  table_name,
  full_namespace,
  storage_path,
  table_type,
  data_source_format,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN
        category = "StorageRead"
        AND requester = 'external'
      THEN
        1
      ELSE 0
    END
  ) as external_read,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN
        category = "StorageWrite"
        AND requester = 'external'
      THEN
        1
      ELSE 0
    END
  ) as external_write,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN
        category = "StorageRead"
        AND requester = 'databricks'
      THEN
        1
      ELSE 0
    END
  ) as uc_read,
  SUM(
    CASE
      WHEN
        category = "StorageWrite"
        AND requester = 'databricks'
      THEN
        1
      ELSE 0
    END
  ) as uc_write,
  CASE
    WHEN
      external_read > 0
      OR external_write > 0
    THEN
      'More Investigation Needed'
    WHEN
      external_read = 0
      OR external_write = 0
    THEN
      'Good Candidate For Managed Table'
  END AS recommendation
FROM
  cte_details
GROUP BY
  subscription_id,
  resource_group,
  storage_account,
  table_catalog,
  table_schema,
  table_name,
  full_namespace,
  storage_path,
  table_type,
  data_source_format

widget.name: 1fa7d8d8
widget.textbox_spec:
# Table Migration Breakdown

This dashboard provides a high-level overview of both registered and unregistered tables, as well as how these tables are being accessed. External tables that are exclusively read and updated via Databricks Unity Catalog (UC) are ideal candidates for conversion to 'managed' tables. However, tables with external readers and writers require further investigation before being moved to ensure that other business processes are not disrupted.

Tables with the name 'foreign' are one where a specific registered table namespace could not be identified. This can happen due to pipeline authorization issues on a storage account, or the underlying table is only available in the storage account.
